Deputy President David Mabuza will answer questions in the National Council of Provinces on Tuesday afternoon. CAPE TOWN - Deputy President David Mabuza will answer questions in the National Council of Provinces on Tuesday afternoon. The NCOP is the upper house of Parliament. Members of the executive are accountable to Parliament for the exercise of powers and performance of their functions. READ: The president was misled about load-shedding, says Mabuza Parliament says it uses a range of instruments to hold the executive accountable, which includes putting questions to the deputy president of the country. Mabuza is set to reply to questions on whether government has developed any implementation timelines for the Renewable Energy Independent Power Producer Procurement Programme. He will also answer a question on whether the issue of South Sudan is resolved.